Staffordshire Police said the officer, who is understood to be from Cannock in Staffordshire, was hurt 'doing his duty'.

He was taken to the trauma unit at Queen Elizabeth Hospital in Birmingham where he is receiving treatment for an eye injury.

Chief Inspector Stephen Morrey said: 'This is a distressing incident whereby one of my officers has been injured whilst protecting members of the public.

'Whilst we are fortunate that incidents like this are very rare, it is a prudent reminder of the danger that officers face daily in their lawful duty to protect members of our communities.

